omers%20bike%20riding%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de34d86080194819fa8cb7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBoomers%20are%20becoming%20less%20likely%20to%20sell%20their%20homes%20and%20move.%3Cp%3EPeter%20Cade%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20internal%20migration%20has%20significantly%20slowed%20over%20the%20last%20five%20decades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELocal%20home%20prices%20influence%20older%20homeowners%20in%20expensive%20states%20less%20than%20in%20past%20decades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20wages%20encouraging%20migration%2C%20housing-related%20factors%20have%20significantly%20offset%20this.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseems-everyone-moving-migration-actually-dramatically-slowed-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFewer%20Americans%20are%20moving%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20the%20US%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-cities-for-retirement-clearwater-florida-arizona-cost-of-living-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboomer%20homeowners%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20more%20expensive%20states%20may%20explain%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32123%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20working%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20economics%20professors%20William%20Olney%20and%20Owen%20Thompson%20at%20Williams%20College%20determined%20that%20residents%20of%20states%20with%20high%20home%20prices%2C%20such%20as%20California%20and%20New%20York%2C%20have%20become%20less%20likely%20to%20move%20as%20a%20result%20of%20those%20high%20prices.%20The%20researchers%20argued%20older%20homeowners%20primarily%20drove%20this%20decline%20in%20internal%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decline%20in%20internal%20migration%20appears%20to%20be%20primarily%20driven%20by%20the%20migration%20decisions%20of%20older%20homeowners%20in%20expensive%20urban%20states%20becoming%20less%20responsive%20to%20local%20home%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20decades%2C%20US%20internal%20migration%20has%20fallen%20substantially.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Ftopics%2Fpopulation%2Fmigration%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Fcps.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20internal%20migration%20has%20slowed%20since%20the%201970s%20amid%20deindustrialization%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-stagflation-explained-oil-outlook-low-growth-high-inflation-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweaker%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20suggests%20that%20declining%20internal%20migration%20is%20due%20to%20changes%20in%20structural%20aspects%20of%20migration%20choice%2C%20which%20affect%20individuals%20and%20families%20of%20many%20different%20backgrounds%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZooming%20out%2C%20the%20researchers%20noted%20that%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-are-workers-moving-sarasota-tampa-florida-texas-linkedin-south-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etend%20to%20migrate%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Northeast%2C%20Midwest%2C%20and%20California%20to%20the%20Northwest%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-economy-us-south-texas-florida-houston-dallas-nashville-miami-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESoutheast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Southwest.%20Net%20migration%20has%20been%20strongest%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-california-moving-to-las-vegas-living-in-seattle-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Illinois%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-north-carolina-retirement-community-loneliness-friends-new-york-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20have%20relatively%20high%20wages%20and%20housing%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENet-positive%20states%20like%20Georgia%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20and%20Texas%20often%20have%20lower%20wages%20and%20housing%20prices.%20Still%2C%20the%20inflow%20rate%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenrys-leaving-west-coast-sunbelt-california-texas-florida-real-estate-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESun%20Belt%20States%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20still%20much%20higher%20than%20most%20other%20states%2C%20has%20declined%20most%20rapidly%20over%20the%2023-year%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20used%20IRS%20administrative%20data%20to%20determine%20why%20migration%20has%20fallen.%20They%20analyzed%20wage%20and%20housing%20price%20gaps%20between%20regions%20around%20big%20cities%20and%20found%20that%20higher%20wages%20tended%20to%20attract%20movers%20from%20lower-wage%20areas%2C%20while%20places%20with%20lower%20housing%20prices%20tended%20to%20bring%20in%20people%20from%20more%20expensive%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20specifically%2C%20a%2010%25%20increase%20in%20the%20origin%20wage%20correlates%20to%20a%203.5%25%20decline%20in%20migration%20as%20people%20are%20more%20inclined%20to%20stay%20in%20areas%20with%20abundant%20high-paying%20jobs.%20When%20wages%20increase%20by%2010%25%20in%20the%20destination%20CZ%2C%20migration%20increases%20by%207.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegarding%20housing%2C%20migration%20rises%201.4%25%20when%20origin%20home%20prices%20rise%2010%25.%20When%20destination%20home%20prices%20grow%2010%25%2C%20migration%20falls%202.6%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20then%20developed%20a%20model%20for%20predicted%20overall%20national%20migration%20rates%20based%20on%20the%20city-to-city%20differences%20in%20wages%20and%20home%20prices%2C%20with%20those%20two%20factors%20alone%20accounting%20for%20about%20a%20third%20of%20moving%20flows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20found%20that%20wages%20on%20their%20own%20could%20have%20pushed%20movers%20to%20migrate%20more%20frequently%2C%20given%20that%20migration%20decisions%20are%20increasingly%20sensitive%20to%20destination%20wages.%20However%2C%20housing-related%20factors%20have%20more%20than%20offset%20wages%20and%20moving%20decisions%20are%20becoming%20less%20influenced%20by%20home%20prices%20in%20their%20current%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20particular%2C%20migration%20has%20become%20much%20less%20responsive%20to%20housing%20prices%20in%20the%20origin%20CZ%2C%20such%20that%20many%20households%20that%20would%20have%20left%20in%20response%20to%20high%20home%20prices%20several%20decades%20ago%20now%20choose%20to%20stay%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20found%20that%20states%20with%20high%20housing%20prices%2C%20including%20California%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20New%20Jersey%2C%20experienced%20the%20greatest%20declines%20in%20sensitivity%20to%20origin%20home%20prices.%20Meanwhile%2C%20renters%2C%20college%20graduates%2C%20and%20younger%20people%20are%20becoming%20slightly%20more%20sensitive%20to%20origin%20home%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20instance%20migration%20is%20significantly%20less%20common%20among%20homeowners%2C%20older%20individuals%2C%20parents%2C%20and%20those%20that%20are%20employed%2C%20while%20it%20is%20significantly%20more%20common%20among%20the%20more%20highly%20educated%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%20homeowners%20also%20experienced%20these%20declines%20most%20profoundly.%20The%20researchers%20suspect%20this%20is%20because%20homeownership%20is%20common%20later%20in%20life%2C%20adding%20that%20older%20Americans%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20hold%20a%20college%20degree.%20These%20homeowners%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20move%20or%20retire%20when%20home%20values%20increase%20in%20their%20current%20location%20compared%20to%2030%20years%20ago.%20Many%20boomers%20are%20moving%20to%20Florida%2C%20Nevada%2C%20and%20Arizona%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fdata-studies%2Fwhere-boomers-moved-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESmartAsset%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fdataviz%2Fvisualizations%2F010%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecensus%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20almost%2020%25%20of%20Americans%20moved%20each%20year%20between%20the%20mid-1940s%20and%20the%201960s%2C%20most%20of%20which%20were%20short%20moves.%20Meanwhile%2C%20in%202022%2C%20the%20overall%20national%20migration%20rate%20was%20just%2012.6%25%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fstories%2F2023%2F11%2Fstate-to-state-migration.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBetween%25202021%2520and%25202022%252C%2520the%2C%252Dto%252Dstate%2520migration%2520flows.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecensus%20data%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20are%20moving%20less%20given%20the%20robust%20job%20market%20that%20has%20brought%20higher-paying%20jobs%20across%20many%20sectors%20to%20many%20corners%20of%20the%20country.%20Still%2C%20bigger%20moves%2C%20such%20as%20cross-country%20moves%2C%20are%20increasing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redfin.com%2Fnews%2Fempty-nesters-own-large-homes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERedfin%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20January%20of%20Census%20Bureau%20data%20found%20that%20in%202022%2C%20empty-nest%20boomers%20owned%2028%25%20of%20US%20homes%20with%20three%20or%20more%20bedrooms.%20This%20is%20about%C2%A0double%20the%2014%25%20share%20owned%20by%20millennials%20with%20kids.%20Many%20boomers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-wont-sell-homes-millennials-kids-need-housing-affordability-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D